  "title" : "Hibernate version?",
  "body" : "<p>I'm using <a href=\"http://community.jboss.org/wiki/EmbeddedJBoss\" rel=\"noreferrer\">JBoss Embedded</a> version beta3.SP10 and I'm facing a persistence bug that is should be fixed in some Hibernate version.  Sadly, I don't know what version of Hibernate is used in my JBoss Embedded and couldn't find a way to find this information, the <code>hibernate-all.jar</code> bundled in it doesn't contain a  <code>org.hibernate.Version</code> class, nor a MANIFEST.</p>\n\n<p>How can I find the currently loaded Hibernate version without using <code>org.hibernate.Version</code>? </p>\n"
